## 6. Built-in Standard Library

### 6.1 Core Modules (Ship with Compiler)

| Module | Functions |
|---|---|
| `std.math` | `min`, `max`, `abs`, `sqrt`, `log2`, `mulDiv`, `fullMul` |
| `std.crypto` | `keccak256`, `sha256`, `ripemd160`, `ecrecover`, `verify` |
| `std.abi` | `encode`, `decode`, `encodePacked`, `encodeWithSelector` |
| `std.address` | `balance`, `code`, `codeHash`, `transfer`, `send`, `call` |
| `std.array` | `push`, `pop`, `length`, `slice`, `contains`, `indexOf` |
| `std.string` | `concat`, `length`, `substr`, `equals`, `toUint`, `toAddress` |
| `std.token` | `ERC20`, `ERC721`, `ERC1155`, `ERC4626` |
| `std.access` | `Ownable`, `AccessControl`, `Roles`, `Timelock` |
| `std.security` | `ReentrancyGuard`, `Pausable`, `RateLimiter` |
| `std.proxy` | `TransparentProxy`, `UUPSProxy`, `MinimalProxy`, `Beacon` |
| `std.governance` | `Governor`, `TimelockController`, `Votes` |
| `std.defi` | `FlashLoan`, `Oracle`, `AMM`, `Vault` |

### 6.2 Example: Full ERC-20 in ZephyrLang

```zephyr
pragma zephyr ^1.0;
import "std.token.ERC20";

contract MyToken is ERC20 {
    role MINTER;

    constructor(string name_, string symbol_) ERC20(name_, symbol_) {
        grant(MINTER, msg.sender);
        _mint(msg.sender, 1_000_000 * 10**decimals());
    }

    function mint(address to, uint256 amount) external only(MINTER) {
        _mint(to, amount);
    }

    function burn(uint256 amount) external {
        _burn(msg.sender, amount);
    }
}
// That's it. ~15 lines for a full, production-ready, mintable/burnable ERC-20.
```

